fix: tray quit left Docker containers running. Root cause was two-fold: (1) server.rs shutdown_signal() only handled SIGINT/Ctrl+C, not SIGTERM which is what Tauri sends when killing the sidecar. Added tokio SIGTERM handler on unix. (2) Tauri shutdown_sidecar() called child.kill() (SIGKILL) which is uncatchable — replaced with SIGTERM via libc::kill + polling try_wait with 15s timeout before SIGKILL fallback. Also removed the xpressclaw down CLI invocation which was fragile (binary path resolution failures were silently ignored).
